H0.text: Air is the resource that a group of frogs living together near a small pond most compete with each other for.

H1.text: Insects are the resource that a group of frogs living together near a small pond compete with each other for the most.

H2.text: Plants are the resource that a group of frogs living together near a small pond compete for most.

H3.text: Sunlight is the resource that a group of frogs living together near a small pond compete with each other for most.

A4.text: Many insects are at least partly aquatic, and have larvae with gills; in some species, the adults too are aquatic.

A5.text: Water beetles and water bugs have legs adapted into paddle-like structures.
